content: For the third quarter, total company revenue totaled $271 million representing a 3% increase over the prior year, excluding the favorable impact at COVID in the prior year, which was estimated at $7 million to $10 million. Matt, with respect to the new contracts, one of the things it's important to keep in mind is that it takes a while in year one for us to actually onboard the business and then achieve ultimate optimal margins, really in year two, and for the remainder of the contract period.
